<file path="docs/api-handbook.json">
{
  "folders": [
    {
      "title": "API Documentation",
      "children": [],
      "pages": [
        {
          "title": "API standards",
          "content": "# API standards — Medbot\n\nMonorepo **pnpm** + **Turborepo**: backend **Express 5** (JavaScript), frontend **Next.js 16** (TypeScript).\n\n## 1. Base path\n* All HTTP routes live under the **/api** prefix (e.g. **/api/auth/login**, **/api/chat/stream**).\n* **No** `/v1`-style version segment in URLs today.\n* Production: the web app usually rewrites **/api/*** to the backend origin via **NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL** (no trailing slash).\n\n## 2. Format\n* Request/response: **JSON**, UTF-8.\n* Body fields use **camelCase** (e.g. **question**, **sessionId**, **isPinned**).\n* Streaming chat: **POST /api/chat/stream** returns **SSE** (`text/event-stream`), not WebSocket.\n\n## 3. HTTP methods (as implemented)\n* **GET**: health, list sessions, history, search logs.\n* **POST**: login, chat (JSON or SSE), session cleanup.\n* **PATCH**: session metadata (title, pinned).\n* **DELETE**: delete session.\n\n## 4. Pagination & query (chat sessions)\n* **GET /api/chat/sessions**: query **limit**, **offset**, **q** (filter title), **pinnedOnly=true**.\n* **GET /api/chat/search**: **q** (minimum 2 characters), **limit**, **offset**.\n\n## 5. Rate limit\n* In-memory middleware per IP; headers **X-RateLimit-Limit**, **X-RateLimit-Remaining**.\n* **429**: body often includes **retryAfterMs** (limit window)."
        },
        {
          "title": "Authentication Flow",
          "content": "# Authentication — JWT\n\n## 1. Mechanism\n* **One JWT** after login (no refresh token in this codebase yet).\n* Payload: **sub** (user id), **email**; signed with **JWT_SECRET**; lifetime **JWT_EXPIRES_IN** (env).\n* Passwords stored with **bcrypt** in **app_users** (Supabase Postgres), RLS enabled; API uses **service role** when it must read/write users.\n\n## 2. Flow\n1. **POST /api/auth/login** — body **{ email, password }** → **{ token, user }**.\n2. Client sends **Authorization: Bearer** with the JWT for protected routes.\n3. **GET /api/auth/me** — Bearer → **{ user: { id, email } }**.\n4. Chat: all **/api/chat/*** except **GET /api/chat/health** require Bearer.\n\n## 3. Security\n* Production: HTTPS.\n* Do not commit secrets; only env templates belong in git."
        },
        {
          "title": "RESTful Endpoints Reference",
          "content": "# Endpoint reference (matches this repo)\n\nBase: API origin (e.g. dev **http://localhost:5000** — from **PORT** env).\n\n## Auth — /api/auth\n* **POST /api/auth/login** — no auth. Body: email, password.\n* **GET /api/auth/me** — Bearer.\n\n## Chat — /api/chat\n* **GET /api/chat/health** — no auth.\n* **POST /api/chat/message** — Bearer. Body: **question**, **sessionId?** → JSON answer.\n* **POST /api/chat/stream** — Bearer. Same body as above → **SSE** (stream_start, stream_chunk, stream_end / stream_error).\n* **GET /api/chat/sessions** — Bearer. Query: limit, offset, q, pinnedOnly.\n* **GET /api/chat/session/:sessionId/history** — Bearer.\n* **GET /api/chat/search** — Bearer. Query: q, limit, offset.\n* **PATCH /api/chat/session/:sessionId** — Bearer. Body: title?, isPinned?\n* **DELETE /api/chat/session/:sessionId** — Bearer.\n* **POST /api/chat/session/:sessionId/cleanup** — Bearer.\n\n## Notes\n* RAG and vector search have **no** separate REST surface — they run inside message/stream handling.\n* Vector knowledge lives in **Zilliz Cloud**, not an upload endpoint in this API."
        },
        {
          "title": "RAG & Vector Search (Medbot)",
          "content": "# RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)\n\n## 1. Concept\n**RAG** augments the LLM answer with knowledge chunks from **Zilliz Cloud** (Milvus): embed question → cosine similarity → top-K → merge into the prompt.\n\n## 2. Chat flow (backend)\n0. **Simple greetings** (hi/hello/hey) → fixed reply, no full LLM call.\n1. **Normalizer**: medical abbreviations (static map + UMLS lookup via scalar filter on Zilliz).\n2. **Embed query**: **@xenova/transformers** Nomic ONNX, **768 dimensions**, prefixes per embedding contract (default **search_query:** + space).\n3. **Search**: Zilliz, **COSINE** metric, **AUTOINDEX**, filter **is_active == true**, score ≥ MIN_RELEVANCE.\n4. **Rerank**: dedupe, boost UMLS/CUI/Q&A, keep **MATCH_COUNT** (5).\n5. **confidence** = average similarity: if **below HIGH_RELEVANCE** (0.65) → OneMin **without** KB, on error Gemini; **from 0.65 up** → OneMin **with** KB.\n\n## 3. Ingest\n* Parquet UMLS (licensed) → **Python** scripts (torch, transformers, **pymilvus**).\n* Document prefix must match contract; upsert: ingest_key, embedding, content, source_type, metadata_json, umls_str_lower, is_active.\n\n## 4. Config (constants)\n* MIN_RELEVANCE_SCORE **0.35**, HIGH_RELEVANCE_SCORE **0.65**, MATCH_COUNT **5**.\n* Changing model/prefix/dim → **re-embed** the whole collection.\n\n## 5. Postgres\n* Supabase stores **chat_sessions**, **chat_logs**, **app_users**, **ingestion_file_state** — **not** RAG vectors."
